definition: to sign one's name/visa/variant of 籤|签[qian1]
inscribed bamboo stick (used in divination, gambling, drawing lots etc)/small wood sliver/label/tag

to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc
variant of 出[chu1] (classifier for plays or chapters of classical novels)

sentences.english: Similarly, suppose you want to do a checkout on a document.
sentences.chinese: 类似地，假设您想在一个文档上执行一个签出操作。

sentences.english: You may need to check out the Actions before you can edit them.
sentences.chinese: 您可能需要首先签出操作，然后才能对其进行编辑。

sentences.english: If you are checking out a branch, that branch becomes your working branch.
sentences.chinese: 如果签出一个分支，则该分支将成为工作分支。

sentences.english: Overwrite writable files that are not checked out to allow the system to overwrite existing files.
sentences.chinese: “覆盖未签出的可写文件”以允许系统覆盖现有文件。

sentences.english: Check out source from a remote code repository.
sentences.chinese: 从一个远程代码存储库中签出源代码。

sentences.english: You need to sign the student out.
sentences.chinese: 您必须在签名簿上将他们签出。

sentences.english: Compare the latest version on the server to the version checked out to you.
sentences.chinese: 比较伺服器上的最新版本与已签出给您的版本。

sentences.english: Compare the copy in your workspace to the version on the server that is checked out to you.
sentences.chinese: 比较工作区中的复本与伺服器上已签出给您的版本。

sentences.english: A check-in lock is less restrictive than a check-out lock.
sentences.chinese: 签入锁的限制少于签出锁。

definition: to issue (a document)/to sign and issue officially
Schengen, village in Luxemburg, location of the 1985 signing of the agreement to create the Schengen area 申根區|申根区[Shen1 gen1 qu1]
to act for sb else/to act on sb's behalf/an agent/a diplomatic representative/a chargé d'affaires
receipt (written acknowledgement of receipt of an item)
to affix a seal/to stamp (a document)/to sign off on sth
